cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this code, data, validation package, or manuscript, please cite this repository and the accompanying paper. The Zenodo DOI is a pre-release placeholder until the first archived GitHub release is created."
type: software
title: "A163665: C17 segmented search and validation package"
authors:
  - family-names: "Corti"
    given-names: "Carlo"
    email: "carlo.corti@outlook.com"
abstract: >-
  C17 segmented search and validation package supporting a computational
  extension of OEIS sequence A163665, the sequence of integers k such that
  k = prime(phi(sigma(pi(k)))). The search is performed over prime indices n
  using the exact fixed-point criterion phi(sigma(n)) = n. The package reports
  eight new terms and records a finite negative certification through
  prime(405234954223) = 11776117514717, subject to the correctness of the
  validated production kernel and the integrity of the recorded official run
  manifest and validation summary.
keywords:
  - OEIS
  - A163665
  - computational number theory
  - integer sequences
  - Euler totient function
  - sum of divisors
  - prime index
  - C17
  - validation
